<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-1054 </DOCNO><TEXT>The article gives a general introduction to automation in mining, past,present and future and describes some of the technology and the applicationsdeveloped so far. These include the SISCOM project (HUNOSA), based onmicroprocessors for the automation of pumps, compressors, and fans; theATEX project developed by IMF based on programmable automats for theautomation of rail transport circuits both underground and on the surface;automated tipping, tub cleaning, loading/un-loading at shaft, crushingand hopper cars; and automation of washeries and winning machines.</TEXT></DOC>